system-config-printer (1.4.3-1endless1) eos; urgency=low

  * debian/patches/endless-Handle-pending-Gtk-events-to-close-the-search-dialog.patch
    - Ensure all gtk events are handled before closing the seach dialog
    - Partial fix for bug https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1052203
  * debian/patches/endless-Don-t-download-OpenPrinting-drivers-in-D-Bus-service.patch
    - Remove the "download drivers from OpenPrinting" feature to avoid deadlock with search dialog
    - Partial fix for bug https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1052203
  * debian/patches/endless-Use-Gtk-main-loop-in-D-Bus-service.patch
    - Avoid locking up after authenticating one printing job.
    - Fix for bug https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1116756
    - Patch needed to apply the last patch in this changeset related to bug 1052203
  * debian/patches/endless-Take-the-gdk-lock-before-entering-gtk_main.patch
    - Avoid deadlocks in the UI by acquiring and releasing the GDK lock properly
    - Partial fix for bug https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1052203

  [endlessm/eos-shell#3182]

